        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 859 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Columbiaville, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northern Lapeer
County, including the following locations... Burnside and Kings Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
